<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.245374>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. A, Trochus indecorus Philippi, 1846, original figure reproduced from Philippi (1848 in 1846 – 1855: pl. 24, fig. 5), diameter 12 linien [= 26 mm]. B – D, Trochus sagittiferus Lamarck, 1822, holotype diameter 22 mm (MHNG, INVE 51508). E, F, Oxystele fulgurata, Saco Mar, Namibe, Angola, height 16.4 mm (images courtesy of P. Ryall). G, H, Oxystele fulgurata, Cabo de Santa Maria, Benguela, Angola, height 23 mm (images courtesy of P. Ryall). I, Trochus fulguratus Philippi, 1849, original figure reproduced from Philippi (1849 in 1846 – 1855: pl. 39, fig. 10), diameter 8.5 linien [= 18.5 mm]. J, Trochus perdix Koch, 1851, original figure reproduced from Philippi (1848 in 1846 – 1855: pl. 24, fig. 17, without legend), diameter 5.5 linien [= 12 mm]. K – M, Trochus variegatus Anton, 1838, lectotype, diameter 12.5 mm (MTD 504), (images courtesy of K. Schniebs). [Images not to scale.]" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/245374/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

